		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/15/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 00:11:40</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3874"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3874')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=8435&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=PoP+spells+%2D+anyone+else+concerned%3F"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Anyone else concerned about the pop spells that were momentarily posted on lucy?  If we were to recieve spells post 60, i would like to at least feel that they were substantial upgrades to our existing spell lines and have either a high level of everyday functional use or be very powerful situational spells.  Quite frankly i didnt see either.</P><P>Here are some issues i saw with them:<BR>- From an overall standpoint of mana efficiency, dps and agro, no dot listed was superior to Funeral pyre in dps or splurt in efficiency.  To boot, the disease and poison dots are rather close to Pox and BoN which are both high resist, high agro spells that are available pre-60 to a shaman.  Why couldnt they just keep progressing our fire line, splurt or introduce a cold based dot?  Instead they're toying around with 2 dots (the poison and dis ones) that i'm assuming most of us would rather not have and may not commonly use.</P><P>- For pets, if the mage epic pet is the best summonable pet in game, it suggests a cap for our post 60 pets with regards to dps, hps, etc...  Assuming the mage epic pet delivers 30percent more dps on avg than our spec pet, it suggests a benchmark to which our pets will be balanced against. I'm guessing that our PoP pets will only be marginally better than our spec pet and if this is not the case, then of course what does this mean for mages and their balance issues?</P><P><BR>I know i dont speak for everyone here, but pets were never really a major component of my game play.  Yes i summon and use when whenever possible, but the fact remains - we are not a class that is reliant upon pets and if that is the case, why introduce 3 pets in our pop list?</P><P>- The darkness upgrade.  Why do we need another dark spell? Its uses on high end mobs is pretty much a mute point (most 60+ mobs are unsnarable or are so MR that landing a darkness cast is 1 in a longshot).  We all know how underused devouring darkness is.  Why give us another spell in this spell line that probably wont be used by the majority of us nec's?  Keep in mind the most popular alternatives have been dooming or epic. Is embracing darkness going to be such an upgrade that we'll either pass on a longer lasting dooming, or a mana free epic click?  /shrug</P><P>I know nothing is set in stone yet and its probably too early to begin ranting on these issues but i do want VI to see my opinions about the PoP spells listed on lucy and hopefully they're shared by many others out there.  As a suggestion, i'd like to recommend extensions of our fire dot line and splurt in addition to a lich upgrade and a cold based dot. If our PoP spell list does indeed look like the one posted on lucy - i'll be greatly disappointed and probably looking at other MMORPG alternatives on the market.</P><P>Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" target="_blank">My Profile</a><BR><a href="http://www.veilofsilence.org" target="_blank">Veil of Silence</a> <BR>Innoruuk Server</font></td>

      </tr>

