        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         With regards to the mage epic being the 'upper cap' to pets...</P><P>With a raised level cap of 65, the power of the players will increase. The weapons and other items that drop will <b>have</b> to be more powerful than those already available in the current high-end game, just to keep people running after the lure. Taking this into account, I would be very hopeful that an extended epic quest system will be put in place.</P><P>Currently, melee epics are being eclipsed by admittedly rare, high-end weapons. Due to the difficulty, and bottlenecks that occur in epic quests, the risk v. reward is being screwed. The same principle can be generally applied to casters. For epics to remain epic, they will need an upgrade in the near future. An 'upgraded' mage epic pet in PoP would permit a raising of the pet power cap, without stepping on the feet of the magi, and would allow the 60+ necromancer pets (and magi pets!) to actually see an increase in power.</P><P>- Drash Theardark - Aquagnome<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
